### Technical Stack

## 1. Backend Stack

### Core Runtime & Framework

* **Node.js** – JavaScript runtime for server-side development
* **Express.js** – Lightweight web framework for REST APIs

### Database & ORM

* **MongoDB** – NoSQL document-based database
* **Mongoose** – ODM for schema design, validation, and relationships

### Authentication & Security

* **JWT (jsonwebtoken)** – Token-based authentication
* **bcrypt** – Password hashing and verification
* **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)** – Admin / Staff separation via middleware

### File Handling

* **Multer** – File uploads (local storage in initial phase)
* **File Metadata Storage** – MongoDB (linked to tasks and clients)

### Environment & Configuration

* **dotenv** – Environment variable management

---

## 2. Frontend Stack

### Core Framework

* **React** – Component-based frontend framework

### Routing & Navigation

* **React Router** – Client-side routing (Admin & Staff dashboards)

### API Communication

* **Axios** – HTTP client for REST API calls

### Styling

* **Tailwind CSS** – Utility-first CSS framework for rapid UI development

### State Management

* **React Hooks** – useState, useEffect, useContext
* **Context API** – Authentication & user role state (initial phase)

---

## 3. Development & Tooling

### Package & Dependency Management

* **npm** – Dependency management

### Version Control

* **Git** – Source control
* **GitHub** – Repository hosting

### API Testing & Debugging

* **Postman** – API testing
* **Browser DevTools** – Frontend debugging

### Database Tools

* **MongoDB Compass** – GUI for MongoDB

### Code Editor

* **Visual Studio Code** – Primary IDE

---

## 4. Deployment (Planned / Optional)

### Backend Deployment

* **Railway / Render / VPS** – Node.js backend hosting

### Frontend Deployment

* **Vercel / Netlify** – React frontend hosting

### Database Hosting

* **MongoDB Atlas** – Managed MongoDB (production)

